headlines.description: — Lamar Stevens spent three quarters watching and waiting his turn. When it finally came, he didn't waste a single second.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 40, Stevens rallies Cavs past Celtics in OT

headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid scores 42, Sixers beat Pacers 147-143 without much D

headlines.shortLinkText: Lillard's triple-double helps Blazers beat Pistons 110-104

headlines.description: — Miami got the breathing room it needed over Atlanta. And now the Heat will take a bit of momentum into trying to chase down others in the Eastern Conference.
headlines.shortLinkText: Butler scores 26, Heat bench adds 59 in 130-128 win vs Hawks

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 24 points, Michael Porter Jr. had 20 and the Denver Nuggets scored the last six points of the game to pull out a 118-113 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray scores 24 points, Nuggets rally past Raptors 118-113

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Sacramento Kings

headlines.description: — Kevin Huerter scored 25 points, Domantas Sabonis had his eighth triple-double of the season and the Sacramento Kings beat the New Orleans Pelicans 123-108 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Huerter has 25, Sabonis a triple-double, Kings beat Pelicans
